Wilamowicean orthography includes the [[Digraph (orthography)|digraph]] "AO", which is treated as a separate letter.

==Sample words and relation to other languages==
A sample of Vilamovian words with German, Dutch and English translations. Note that '''<U+0142>''' is read in Vilamovian like English '''w''' (as in Polish), and '''w''' like '''v''' (as in Polish and German):

