==Sample texts==
[[Lord's Prayer]] in Vilamovian

{{quote|Ynzer Foter, d<U+00FC> byst ym hymu<U+0142>,

Daj noma zu<U+0142> zajn gywajt;

Daj  Kyngrajch zu<U+0142> d<U+00F6> kuma;

Daj wy<U+0142>a zu<U+0142> zajn ym hymu<U+0142> an uf der aot;

dos ynzer gywyn<U+0142>ichys brut gao yns haojt;

an fercaj yns ynzer siu<U+0142>da,

wi wir aoj fercajn y ynzyn siu<U+0142>digia;

ny <U+0142>at yns cyn zynda;

zunder kaonst yns reta fum nistg<U+00FC>ta.

[Do  Dajs  ej z  Kyngrajch an dy maocht, ans <U+0142>aowa uf inda.]

Amen}}

A [[lullaby]] in Vilamovian with English translation:

{{quote|<U+015A><U+0142><U+00F6>f maj buw<U+0142>a fest!

Skumma fremdy gest,

Skumma muma ana fettyn,

Z' brennia nys<U+0142>a ana epu<U+0142>n,

<U+015A><U+0142><U+00F6>f maj Jasiu fest!

Sleep, my boy, soundly!

Foreign guests are coming,

Aunts and uncles are coming,

Bringing nuts and apples,

Sleep, my Johnny, soundly!}}

